84
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:06,599
Got it?

85
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,439
Take a seat.

86
00:08:21,319 --> 00:08:22,159
Order whatever you want.

87
00:08:22,399 --> 00:08:22,899
No thanks,

88
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,479
I already ate.

89
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:25,720
Just say what you have to say.

90
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:28,319
Uh...

91
00:08:28,319 --> 00:08:28,880
I...

92
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,020
wait a second.

93
00:08:35,479 --> 00:08:36,359
You really have to record this?

94
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,279
It’s for my dad. He needs to know the truth.

95
00:08:41,199 --> 00:08:42,600
Go on. Apologize.

96
00:08:43,239 --> 00:08:43,800
Fine.

97
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:45,720
 I’m sorry. 

98
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:47,720
Your dessert was excellent, Nabtang

99
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:50,920
But... I’m talking about the second time.

100
00:08:55,359 --> 00:08:58,439
Was the first time really that salty?

101
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,039
But why should I believe you?

102
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:05,960
But why should I believe you?

103
00:09:09,399 --> 00:09:09,899
What is it?

104
00:09:12,239 --> 00:09:13,479
I have my grandfather's restaurant 

105
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:15,119
on Baimai Khram Island.

106
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,000
Would you like to be my chef?"

107
00:09:19,239 --> 00:09:20,439
Why me? 

108
00:09:21,319 --> 00:09:22,800
You never even believed in my cooking.

109
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:27,079
These are the three conditions set by Mr. Anan.

110
00:09:27,319 --> 00:09:31,039
If you fulfill all three conditions...

111
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:34,239
...you will have full rights to the inheritance.

112
00:09:34,359 --> 00:09:39,840
First: You must run the restaurant for one full year.

113
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:44,239
Second: You must manage the restaurant in person.

114
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:48,840
And finally: Mr. Anan has already specified 

115
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,840
the person he wants as the head chef.

116
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:56,800
This person is...

117
00:10:03,159 --> 00:10:07,119
This is weird. Is this a scam? I'm not doing it.

118
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:10,960
You'll have total creative control over the menu.

119
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,319
And?

120
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,880
Anything else?

121
00:10:20,079 --> 00:10:21,800
Because it still sounds pretty boring.

122
00:10:23,079 --> 00:10:24,039
If you complete the year,

123
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:28,600
I’ll give you a five-million-baht bonus.

124
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,239
When do you need an answer?

125
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:34,600
As soon as possible.

126
00:10:39,279 --> 00:10:40,119
Can I ask you something?

127
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,399
Why the sunglasses indoors?

128
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,479
It's a style choice.

129
00:10:46,239 --> 00:10:47,560
One step away from being a lottery seller.

130
00:10:48,079 --> 00:10:50,199
And the prize goes to... 

131
00:11:10,479 --> 00:11:11,640
You're actually kind of cute, you know.

132
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:16,159
You just need to look longer.

133
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:25,239
Give this a try.

134
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,279
Let me know if you like it.

135
00:11:29,279 --> 00:11:29,840
I'm leaving now.

136
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,319
I'll take two chicken legs, please.

137
00:11:48,359 --> 00:11:48,859
Sure thing.

138
00:12:15,439 --> 00:12:16,600
This is amazing!

139
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,960
What kind of chicken is this?

140
00:12:20,319 --> 00:12:21,760
I've never tasted anything like it.

141
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:25,760
It's definitely not Hat Yai fried chicken.

142
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:29,079
"This is Ma-khwaen fried chicken.

143
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,239
 It’s a specialty from Nan.

144
00:12:34,199 --> 00:12:37,479
You don't look Thai at all.

145
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:40,239
How is your Thai so clear?

146
00:12:41,199 --> 00:12:43,359
I'm mixed—half Korean, actually.

147
00:12:44,199 --> 00:12:46,359
But I've lived in Thailand for years now.

148
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:49,479
It's my first time here,

149
00:12:51,439 --> 00:12:53,680
though. Enjoy your trip!

150
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,039
I'm actually here for work.

151
00:12:57,439 --> 00:12:59,960
But if I'm free, I'll visit often.

152
00:13:01,239 --> 00:13:02,039
It's so good!

153
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:04,560
 You're very welcome.

154
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:22,020
Yes, boss.

155
00:13:24,239 --> 00:13:25,600
Regarding the signature menu... 

156
00:13:26,399 --> 00:13:26,899
I've got it.

157
00:13:28,439 --> 00:13:30,560
Just let me tweak the recipe a bit, 

158
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,319
then I'll let you taste it.

159
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:34,000
yes

160
00:13:51,399 --> 00:13:53,439
Khao Khluk Kapi Bibimbap

161
00:13:56,159 --> 00:13:58,640
Are you just going to stare, or are you going to try some?

162
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:19,520
Looking for someone?

163
00:15:24,359 --> 00:15:27,960
No. I just came to order a drink.

164
00:15:29,039 --> 00:15:31,840
Wait a sec. I have a new drink for you to try.

165
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,560
Feel free to criticize.

166
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:08,560
How is it?

167
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:11,239
It's delicious.

168
00:16:12,319 --> 00:16:14,680
But... it's got quite a kick.

169
00:16:18,399 --> 00:16:19,239
Just like you. 

170
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,119
Sweet, beautiful...

171
00:16:24,479 --> 00:16:25,319
but with a hidden spice.

172
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:29,119
You even know the word 'Zapp'?

173
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:31,520
Of course. 

174
00:16:41,119 --> 00:16:44,359
Is something wrong, Q? You look sad.

175
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:52,880
My dad is forcing me to go back to Thailand.

176
00:17:06,199 --> 00:17:08,840
I don't want to go. 

177
00:17:13,439 --> 00:17:15,680
I’m so happy here, Karn.

178
00:17:18,199 --> 00:17:21,800
I’m free here. I can be whoever I want to be.

179
00:17:23,640 --> 00:17:24,640
When do you leave?

180
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,520
 In about two or three days.

181
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:33,760
That’s so soon. 

182
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,880
I’m going to miss you, Q.

183
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:49,439
I’ll miss you too.

184
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,560
This is really good.

185
00:18:15,119 --> 00:18:16,039
Want one?

186
00:18:16,039 --> 00:18:16,960
no

187
00:18:17,159 --> 00:18:17,800
give it a try.

188
00:18:18,159 --> 00:18:19,079
no

189
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,800
How about this one?

190
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:28,600
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner...

191
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:31,560
that I'm a chef.

192
00:19:40,479 --> 00:19:41,079
Karn...

193
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,560
will you be with me?

194
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:48,840
My mother is gone.

195
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:05,079
Hiring two chefs.

196
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:07,079
"I want to work here.

197
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:13,079
I made a promise to someone.

198
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,159
And I really liked this island.

199
00:20:16,239 --> 00:20:19,680
You really do look like a thug, 

200
00:20:20,399 --> 00:20:21,600
don't you? For a market owner."

201
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:25,680
I like your feistiness.

202
00:20:27,279 --> 00:20:27,779
It’s hot.

